f=AI & Agents/relay/operational/commands/relay-commands.md · h1:relay — Command Triggers=\| Trigger phrases \| Skill \| Shortcut \| · h1:relay — Command Triggers=\|---\|---\|---\| · h1:relay — Command Triggers=\| "connect mcp", "new tool", "register tool", "tool access", "what's connected", "revoke" \| mcp-tool-registry \| /register \| · h1:relay — Command Triggers=\| "who can call", "grant access", "access audit", "does X need this" \| least-privilege-grants \| /grants \| · h1:relay — Command Triggers=\| "egress", "allowlist", "sandbox domains", "blocked domain", "denied call" \| egress-allowlist-authoring \| /egress \| · h1:relay — Command Triggers=\| "integration design", "retry", "idempotent", "circuit breaker", "tool keeps failing", "contract drift" \| integration-patterns \| /integrate \| · h2:Precedence=Incident language ("blocked", "denied", "suspicious") egress-allowlist-authoring's reconcile path first. "New tool" always starts mcp-tool-registry (registration precedes grants, grants precede integration review). Grants questions inside registration flow stay least-privilege-grants; registry records.